name: Tater Tot Hot Dish II
author: VANORNUM
summary: This is an old recipe, easy and kids usually like it.  If you like, add green beans over the hamburger and skip the onion rings if desired.
ingredients: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of mushroom soup
1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of celery soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
In a large skillet cook ground beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain and spread into the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish
Add tater tots; mix cream of mushroom and cream of celery soup together and pour mixture over dish
Top with onion rings, if using
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour
